    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> EDIT1<br />
Ranger&#39;s Sword is the new one &quot;Blade Of Aragorn&quot;<br />
END EDIT1<br />
<br />
OOOPS<br />
Forgot about my Sites....here they are:<br />
[1]Western Emyn Muil (exert Ringbounds)<br />
[2]Wold of Rohan (give me TW)<br />
[3]Golden Hall <br />
[4]White Mountains (2 Wounds 4 you)<br />
[5]Deep Of Helm (Archer swarm)<br />
[6]Caves Oeasterlinglarond (my archers are fierce)<br />
[7]Hornburg Causeway (ARCHERY!!)<br />
[8]Wizard&#39;s Vale<br />
[9]Balcony Of Orthanc (2 Burden to get more archers)<br />
<br />
Strategy<br />
Well,with this deck i want to kill,but i can also race.<br />
Eowyn can use symbelmines and get me Eomer and his stuff.Legolas is still the man,he shoots those Moria,Dunland and burdenmaking Raiders and of courde Cantea.Aragorn chokes and joins Legolas when equipped with his bow.Boromir heals...this is very important against uruk Archeryheal him twice, so you can soak up even more wounds next turn. Faramir kills Nazghul.Give him two brands and last alliance and he&#39;s the man.He is an incredible fighter.Sam gets rid of burdens, if they manage to make some.Merry helps to win key skirmishes.Eomer is just too good not to use,so he joins as my ninth companion.Equiped with Firefoot and his spear he is a all killing killer machine, especially when you shoot well with Legolas and Aragorn.Ranger&#39;s sword gives Aragorn power, espessially against Uruks.Sting is just as good as always.Sting gives you pool control angainst orcs and helps frodo surviving.Filibert is killer!He has to be in every deck!With the help of Galadriel you can heal Orophin and Rumil, and sentinel conditions away.She also helps to have some pool control, playing your elves for free.Elrond heals,so you can shoot more or boost more with Merry or......!Last Alliance pumps up your fighters and secret sentinels are just too important not to play.I chose elves instead of gandalf, because of Secret sentinels.The most important fact is that SS can dircard conditions immeately.E.G. you played a weapons of Isengard...hmm, i&#39;ll discard them, before you get to use them.Same with Dunland and their No Retreat thing.Of course I know that Sleep or Grown Suddenly Tall kicks every condition but i found out that if you kill their key conditions that&#39;s game.But i am thinking in going up to four sentinels, but i just don&#39;t know what to throw out.Ok,that&#39;s enough talk about our brave party, let&#39;s talk about the ugly way of winning.<br />
<br />
Uruk Crossbow Troop is just killer, because one crossbow troop and one machine and you got three archery for only six TW!It is also an power eight minion and that means it can win skirmishes.Uruk crossbowman are cheap archers that are able to wound(!) unbound companions, so it is provided that frodo won#t soak up all wounds you make.Ranged Commander is your swarmer.With him and some TW you are able to drop a bunch of archers,and he also can wound unbounds.Elite crossbowmen are expensive, but you can wound unbound companions twice(!) and they are power nine, so they might win their skirmishes.Orthanc Assasin is a power 10 archer for  5 TW and that&#39;s fine with me.Lurtz is a five wound potencial minion so why shouldn&#39;t i play two?I thought about playing three Lurtz,but i think that would be overkill.Desert Lord can exert companions, and he can do it with ringbounds, so he will be the one that exerts faramirs and Sams.I hate it when people take archery fire as burdens and then remove them with Sam.I prefer the burden to stay where they are,and once they are thereb Enquea shows up.He is also a five wound potential minion.Watch out for Legolas and Aragorn with his bow.Wound em first.Than Enquea might win his skirmishes too.If  he prevents the wound with eowyn...well...that doesn&#39;t matter.a wound is a wound.if he starts playing billions of companions and you just can&#39;t enquea them away and they can handle your archers(which by the way is almost impossible with the TW you&#39;ll get) there is Greed, a card that makes wounds out of nothing and the 2 TW shouldn&#39;t be a problem with your four copys of Tower of Orthanc.They&#39;ll have some exhausted companions very soon.If they haven&#39;t you have to use desert Lord e.g. or assign your minions right via saruman.he can finish off many many companions.Legolas ehausted?You won&#39;t assign him?I will.If he exerts to prevent some assignments that are more wound for him.well...weapons of Isengard are two archery for two TW...awesome.And last but not least driven back  is just soooooooo killer, i can&#39;t explain it.Try it.+1 archery for each card in the dead pile...:D.<br />
If he manages to get to site 9 there ARE some companions in the dead pile (lets say four or five,which is little)you get +5 archery for three TW!!!!<br />
<br />
Possible matchups:<br />
Ok, fist of all I have to say that in my area there is this moria site 7 cavern entrance beatdown deck, tha&#39;s why i don&#39;t play gandalf, servants etc.i prefer Archery and SS to get rid of their Armorys, Swarms etc.<br />
<br />
Moria:Use SS, shoot wisely and kill em with your shadow.<br />
Dunland: You just have to win jkey skirmishes.Shoot extemly wisly and skirmish well.Take your time to think.Sometimes it is better to give them a site, sometimes it is better letting them discard weaopns.<br />
Uruk Beatdown:I think of 4saruman,KOI regulars all the 3 cost minions and deep of helm,DON&#39;T DOUBLE MOVE! Kill em, cuz they need a lot of card drawing to get the eight shadow cars they need at 5, so their fellowship is weak, and their stealths won&#39;t help to archery.<br />
Uruk Tracker:Can be very effective, espessialy at the early sites.But you don&#39;t have to run...you will kill your opponent with your shadow.<br />
Uruk Archery:Difficult.Use your brain and DON&#39;T RUN!heal Boromir every turn, and watch out for saruman so boromir won&#39;t die.use healing elrond.and kill him.<br />
against raider:There are some really good raider decks, and i got killed by one because it made seven burden in one turn,but that&#39;s not normal!! :) Shoot the burdenmaker once, so they can&#39;t make em. Try to assign em to faramir,so they can&#39;t use their game text and kill em with a fully equipped faramir.<br />
<br />
Well ok, that&#39;s it.<br />
Have fun.<br />
And dmail me with your suggenstions or email me Liamtan@web.de<br />
awainting your critisism<br />
Liamtan  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php?PHPSESSID=b79c46923ce6c0ff5b8c6e4d4cf7c573">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=26581&PHPSESSID=b79c46923ce6c0ff5b8c6e4d4cf7c573"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=26581&PHPSESSID=b79c46923ce6c0ff5b8c6e4d4cf7c573" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=b79c46923ce6c0ff5b8c6e4d4cf7c573">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
